peopleAlsoAsk.question: How old are secretary desks?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Secretary Desk The secretary bookcase, or secrétaire, was an innovative piece of writing furniture introduced in the early 18th century. For the wealthiest households, the secretary desk proved to be the preferred place to write, transcribe and store written treasures.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do I date an old school desk?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: To date a desk, first look for any stamps or labels that tell you the name of the company that produced it. You can then use the maker information to research the piece using trusted online resources.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: When were secretary desks made?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The secretary desk has a rich history that dates back to the 17th century. It originated in France and quickly spread throughout Europe, becoming a staple in many households. Early secretary desks were often decorated with intricate carvings and embellishments, showcasing the craftsmanship of the time.
